
                     ------------------------------------
                       Verigames XML Visualization Tool
                     ------------------------------------

This tool lets you visualize world XML files. It outputs a bunch of SVG images
(one per level) to a folder of your choice.


Building
-------------

Follow the setup instructions in the "USING_GRADLE" file one level up. Then, in
this folder:

    gradle jar

This will generate the file build/libs/visualizer.jar which the start script
uses to run the tool (see "Running" below).


Running
-------------

Get help:

    ./visualizer.sh --help

Sample usage:

    ./visualizer.sh --out myfolder <../Translation/veritest/layout/GETLayoutTest.expected.xml

This produces a bunch of awesome output images in "myfolder".


Hacking
-------------

All the source is written in Java, and it all lives in src/main/java (which is
the default expected source path for Gradle's Java plugin).
